<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="165" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/182.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 3. Presidential rescript just issued extending Huai River
                            option for one year.</p>
                        <p>Minister Shah transmitted several suggestions for amendment of the
                            proposed contract which the Minister of Commerce discussed with me and
                            which I believe I convinced him to be utterly impracticable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>